  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2141",
  "title": "[docs] Searching in docs does not jump to correct place in page",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nBug\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the current behavior?**\r\nWhen on https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/documentation/, If I search (eg. `label`), and click on the result or select it through the keyboard, nothing happens. I'm not redirected to the correct part of the doc.\r\n\r\n![2017-05-16_11h26m07](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/283419/26099246/7dd6500e-3a2a-11e7-9551-69f716261cac.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the expected behavior?**\r\nI would expect the page to jump to the selected part of the page/\r\n\r\n**Bug: What browsers are impacted? Which versions?**\r\nTested on Chrome Version 57.0.2987.133 (64-bit) on Ubuntu\r\n\r\n**Bug: What is the proposed solution?**\r\nSelecting a result should jump to the correct part. Maybe it's time to use DocSearch on this website?",
